WEBVTT

00:06.082 --> 00:17.294
The Holy Spirit in utter allegiance to this mission given him by the Father and the Son will not quicken a heart to see nothing.

00:18.896 --> 00:23.121
He will only quicken hearts to see Christ.

00:24.202 --> 00:30.950
Therefore, if Christ is not placarded, the Holy Spirit will not open the eyes of the blind.

00:31.731 --> 00:34.834
He is utterly devoted to the glory of the Son.

00:35.362 --> 00:46.615
And therefore, when we preach the Son, the Holy Spirit comes and says, that is what I want people to see, I will open their eyes to it.

00:46.635 --> 00:52.081
There's a kind of preaching that leaves you moved, but you're not sure exactly why.

00:52.822 --> 01:01.232
And then there's preaching that makes Jesus so clear, so beautiful that your heart knows it's the Spirit at work.

01:01.933 --> 01:02.834
I'm Dan Kruver.

01:03.042 --> 01:11.755
In this episode of Light and Truth, John Piper shows why the spirit opens eyes only when Christ is held high.

01:12.476 --> 01:19.046
This message was originally delivered in Wheaton, Illinois at the Act III Reformation Conference on October 28, 1999.

01:24.555 --> 01:25.777
First a word about man.

01:26.858 --> 01:31.826
Perhaps the title should be a little more crazy and

01:32.578 --> 01:43.074
radical than it is because if I was standing in the lobby of the holiday in about 30 minutes ago watching CNN while they cleaned our room so we could get in.

01:44.816 --> 01:56.834
And after I watched it, I thought, you know, the title of this pre-conference should probably be preaching God in a primate centered age.

02:01.141 --> 02:01.842
Because

02:02.178 --> 02:16.841
Here is this demonstration against doing experimental drugs on monkeys, precisely because monkeys have no more right or less right to be treated with dignity than you do.

02:19.745 --> 02:24.172
That's a serious change in the seascape of American culture.

02:26.776 --> 02:30.802
We hold these truths to be self-evident and so on that man, this or that.

02:31.650 --> 02:39.818
So preaching in a man-centered age is more serious than we thought it was.

02:40.679 --> 02:44.943
It's really man slash monkey-centered age.

02:46.805 --> 02:50.529
And that makes my sense of urgency all the greater.

02:51.450 --> 02:52.411
That's a word on man.

02:53.572 --> 03:00.018
A word on preaching, I love to preach.

03:01.282 --> 03:15.680
It is my life and I love to preach in the context of the local church and I love to preach in the context of worship, corporate worship.

03:15.700 --> 03:26.994
I would rather preach in my church than do what I'm doing right now any day of the week because I love to preach to a flock of people in worship.

03:28.322 --> 03:34.310
that build week after week after week upon common visions of who God is.

03:35.312 --> 03:41.961
So know that I'm coming to you as utterly and totally biased toward preaching.

03:43.744 --> 03:44.825
That's the word on preaching.

03:46.087 --> 03:50.834
The word on God is that I love God more than I love preaching.

03:52.516 --> 03:54.819
I love God as my Creator.

03:55.961 --> 03:56.722
I love

03:56.866 --> 04:01.493
to contemplate God as my maker.

04:01.513 --> 04:10.627
I love to contemplate God as my sustainer, moment by moment.

04:10.647 --> 04:13.972
Life and breath and everything comes from Him.

04:14.914 --> 04:22.586
If my heart keeps beating until the end of this message, it will be a freely given gift of my maker.

04:22.606 --> 04:25.330
And I love Him for treating me that way.

04:25.634 --> 04:27.156
and for being that for me.

04:27.597 --> 04:42.739
I love him as my Savior, that he has sent his Son into the world to cover all my sins and work out a perfect righteousness for me and impute it to me through the mere leaning on him alone.

04:43.840 --> 04:53.234
I love him as my keeper and the portion that I expect to enjoy with ever increasing gladness forever and ever.

04:54.018 --> 04:56.161
So this is an easy task for me, frankly.

04:56.662 --> 05:05.014
This is very easy to extol preaching, to preach God, to preach to people who think monkeys are equal to man.

05:05.074 --> 05:06.897
This is not a hard thing to do.

05:07.718 --> 05:12.685
And I just want to ask now that God would come and put his anointing on this word.

05:13.566 --> 05:17.272
So let's go to him and ask him to do it.

05:17.292 --> 05:21.778
Oh, Father in Heaven, this is a very precious moment.

05:22.818 --> 05:48.137
When pastor to pastor, we can extol together the glory of God in the preached word to people so adrift that they don't even know who they are created in the image of God destined for everlasting damnation or everlasting glory.

05:48.718 --> 05:50.020
They don't have a clue.

05:50.040 --> 05:51.442
They don't know their right hand.

05:51.810 --> 05:52.791
from their left.

05:55.034 --> 05:57.256
Our calling is so serious.

05:59.158 --> 06:03.683
Would you grant now a sense of earnestness, seriousness in this hour?

06:04.244 --> 06:06.646
And would you help me, Lord Jesus, help me?

06:07.788 --> 06:17.899
To say what I ought to say concerning this matter, help Tom after me and help us to listen, make us docile to the word truth.

06:18.259 --> 06:20.722
Keep us close to your word.

06:21.826 --> 06:24.029
Come now I pray and help us in Jesus name.

06:24.871 --> 06:25.131
Amen.

06:27.494 --> 06:36.528
I'm going to read a text and if you want to turn there with me in your Bibles 2 Timothy chapter 3 or 16 to chapter 4 verse 5.

06:37.209 --> 06:48.626
My topic to begin is the place of preaching or preaching this great God in the context of worship, corporate worship.

06:57.026 --> 06:58.689
2 Timothy 3, 16.

06:59.710 --> 07:15.193
All scripture is inspired by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, for training in righteousness, so that the man of God may be adequate, equipped for every good work.

07:15.213 --> 07:26.290
I solemnly charge you in the presence of God and of Christ Jesus, who is to judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing in his kingdom, preach the word.

07:27.586 --> 07:35.878
Be ready in season and out of season, reprove, rebuke, exhort with great patience and instruction.

07:37.441 --> 07:43.369
For the time will come, they will not endure sound doctrine but wanting to have their ears tickled.

07:44.892 --> 07:57.330
They will accumulate for themselves teachers in accordance with their desires and will turn away their ears from the truth and will turn aside to myths.

08:01.506 --> 08:12.862
And here's the question I'm asking, why preaching assumes such a prominent place in corporate worship?

08:14.544 --> 08:22.875
Is this just habit and tradition, or is there a warrant for it, biblically and theologically?

08:22.935 --> 08:24.257
Is it rooted in Scripture?

08:24.317 --> 08:30.706
Is it rooted in God that probably in this pulpit, Sunday by Sunday, I would guess that

08:31.010 --> 08:39.182
Almost half probably of the service is devoted to the exposition of the Word of God as it is in my church.

08:40.624 --> 08:50.419
I preach about 40 minutes or so every Sunday, following almost as long, singing and praying.

08:51.621 --> 08:53.063
Why do we do it that way?

08:53.083 --> 09:00.274
Why does this task of preaching assume such a prominent role

09:00.418 --> 09:02.861
incorporate worship.

09:04.863 --> 09:05.664
That's my question.

09:07.286 --> 09:12.072
And there are several kinds of answers that you can give.

09:15.236 --> 09:16.457
It's really two questions.

09:16.978 --> 09:17.699
Let me divide it.

09:18.920 --> 09:24.027
It's a question of why is the Word so prominent?

09:24.848 --> 09:26.770
Why is the Word of God

09:27.714 --> 09:36.205
And then this particular form, question two, this particular way of speaking or handling the word of God called preaching.

09:36.606 --> 09:40.551
First, why is the words of prominent in corporate worship?

09:40.571 --> 09:45.197
And then why is this way of doing it so prominent?

09:45.217 --> 09:47.260
So let's take those one at a time.

09:48.481 --> 09:51.966
And these are real basic and real obvious answers.

09:52.046 --> 09:54.930
I think I'll pass over part of the answer, I think.

09:55.202 --> 10:10.539
Not wanting to tread on any of Vatam's territory about Jesus is the Word and goes straight to the simple, straightforward question or observation of chapter 3, verse 16 here.

10:12.822 --> 10:13.502
Second Timothy.

10:14.403 --> 10:19.809
All Scripture is inspired by God.

10:22.292 --> 10:24.114
That is an amazing state.

10:25.218 --> 10:27.602
You really got to come to terms with this, brothers.

10:28.223 --> 10:30.386
You have to come to terms with this.

10:31.187 --> 10:32.489
Do you believe that?

10:33.671 --> 10:45.088
That this book, my little NASV updated paperback, this book is God Breathe.

10:45.349 --> 10:51.778
If that is true, if that is true, everything changes in the world.

10:52.960 --> 10:54.162
What you do, ministry?

10:54.946 --> 11:10.060
What you say in ministry, the way you counsel, the way you do funerals, the way you do weddings, the way you stand by hospital beds, the way you live your life, the way you handle your sexuality, the way you handle your money, the way you handle your community life.

11:10.320 --> 11:22.031
Everything changes for the saints and for the pastor especially if it's true that the Bible is a God-breathed book, which I believe that it is.

11:23.693 --> 11:24.754
No prophecy.

11:25.090 --> 11:36.525
was ever made by an act of human will, but men moved by the Holy Spirit, spoke and I believe you could say, wrote from God.

11:37.747 --> 11:54.770
So my first reason for why the Bible or the Word is prominent in worship is that God breathed this book and therefore when the book is read or studied or explained or heralded

11:55.490 --> 11:57.373
God is speaking.

11:57.393 --> 12:08.249
If it's done accurately and handled well, and when God is speaking, God is revealed, and when God is revealed, people worship.

12:08.269 --> 12:14.078
You cannot worship apart from communing with God through the Word.

12:14.679 --> 12:25.074
Worship that undertakes to do an in-run around the revelation of God through the Bible will become defective worship very quickly.

12:25.602 --> 12:30.167
Worship hangs on the centrality of the Word.

12:31.529 --> 12:34.432
So that's my first reason.

12:34.452 --> 12:35.413
Here's the second one.

12:36.995 --> 12:52.031
Worship is a response to the work of God, not just the self-revelation through Word, but that Word describing and doing the work of God.

12:53.073 --> 12:54.354
It points to God

12:54.466 --> 12:58.512
It is God's Word and gives it insight into his character and personality.

12:58.853 --> 13:02.138
It describes works of God, but here's what I'm getting at.

13:02.999 --> 13:08.768
The Word doesn't just portray God.

13:09.008 --> 13:11.852
It performs the work of God.

13:12.113 --> 13:17.962
The Word depicts God and does the work of God.

13:18.583 --> 13:23.410
It expresses God's will and way and character.

13:23.586 --> 13:30.673
and it effects God's will and His way in the world.

13:31.394 --> 13:38.321
You see this all over the old and the new Testament from creation on Hebrews 11, 3.

13:38.741 --> 13:43.066
By faith we know that the worlds were made by the Word of God.

13:43.126 --> 13:51.314
So this whole world, glorious October fall that makes my spine tingle as I look at front campus where I

13:53.282 --> 13:56.005
had so many spiritual breakthroughs 30 years ago.

13:58.148 --> 13:59.669
God made that front campus.

13:59.850 --> 14:01.371
God made those yellow trees.

14:02.032 --> 14:03.914
God made the sky and the sun.

14:04.695 --> 14:06.397
God did that with a word.

14:07.719 --> 14:15.027
He just spoke and it was and he holds it in being by his word according to Hebrews chapter 1.

14:15.988 --> 14:20.754
But there's a more immediate application to this here in the text that I read to you.

14:21.954 --> 14:49.906
He doesn't just do his word, Jesus didn't just do his work by the word, though he did, fevers were cooled by the word, and lepers were cleansed by the word, and seas were calmed by the word, and the eyes of the blind were opened by the word, but there's something more immediately relevant for us in this text, and let me read it to you.

14:50.658 --> 15:15.184
2 Timothy 3, 16 and 17, all Scripture is inspired by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, for training and righteousness, so that the man of God might be adequate, fitted out and equipped for every good work.

15:16.426 --> 15:19.369
So where does the work of God come from?

15:19.409 --> 15:20.370
It comes from

15:20.674 --> 15:28.221
the fitting power of the Word, the equipping power of the Word, the transforming power of the Word.

15:28.462 --> 15:44.757
And if you relate this now to something Jesus said in Matthew 5, 16, let your light so shine before man that they may see your good deeds and give glory to your Father in heaven.

15:45.098 --> 15:45.878
That's worship.

15:46.919 --> 15:49.682
Giving glory to God in heaven is worship.

15:49.890 --> 15:51.052
And where did it come from?

15:51.072 --> 15:55.959
It came from beholding the works of the people of God in the world.

15:56.220 --> 15:59.224
And where do the works of the people of God in the world come from?

15:59.525 --> 16:06.596
According to verse 17 of 2 Timothy 3, they come from being fitted out by the Word of God.

16:07.297 --> 16:18.674
So if you want to both preach in the context of worship as well as beget a worshiping people and a worship producing people, you stay with the Word.

16:20.130 --> 16:21.071
You stay with the Word.

16:21.091 --> 16:41.661
If you want your people to be so transformed that they live radical, different lives that make the world see something of God and give Him glory, then according to this logic, moving from 2 Timothy 3 17 to Matthew 5 16 to the glory of God, you stay with the Word.

16:41.781 --> 16:42.782
You preach the Word.

16:43.563 --> 16:48.370
You unfold the Word and you do it with all your might.

16:51.810 --> 16:53.732
Oh, there's so much more evidence we could give.

16:53.752 --> 17:01.060
Let me, I'm going to pass over Psalm 1 and Hebrews 4 and just sum up this first point with this.

17:02.702 --> 17:18.258
Worship is about knowing and admiring and savoring God through his self-revelation in his word and by his works, which are produced by his word.

17:19.586 --> 17:29.881
Worship comes from seeing God and savoring God, seeing and savoring.

17:29.901 --> 17:41.657
And therefore the Word, which is where we see Him, how we come to taste, taste and see, savoring.

17:41.677 --> 17:44.201
And therefore we stay with the Word and make it central.

17:44.221 --> 17:47.986
But now that's only part of the answer

17:48.098 --> 17:49.600
to why it's crucial for worship.

17:50.801 --> 18:11.343
It's crucial for worship, the centrality of the word, because on the other side of this pulpit, there are people who are not going to see God and savor God apart from the quickening work of the Holy Spirit.

18:11.363 --> 18:13.406
There has to be life in the pew.

18:15.948 --> 18:17.490
There has to be new birth.

18:18.018 --> 18:19.980
There has to be spiritual quickening.

18:20.040 --> 18:24.666
The natural man does not receive what passes from this side to that side.

18:25.067 --> 18:25.988
It's not welcomed.

18:26.048 --> 18:26.989
It's not savored.

18:27.389 --> 18:28.491
It's not understood.

18:28.551 --> 18:34.838
It's considered foolishness or a stumbling block, unless the Holy Spirit does some transforming.

18:36.661 --> 18:37.241
New birth.

18:38.743 --> 18:43.109
And where does that come from?

18:43.129 --> 18:44.130
1 Peter 1, 23.

18:45.772 --> 18:47.634
You have been born again.

18:48.066 --> 18:54.072
not of seed which is perishable, but imperishable.

18:54.092 --> 19:00.758
That is, through the living and enduring word of God.

19:02.460 --> 19:04.021
This is the gospel which we preach.

19:06.604 --> 19:17.394
Now, we reformed types, and I know that this conference does not presume that everybody becomes is a reformed type, but I am.

19:17.698 --> 19:24.065
One, we reform types need to be admonished and exhorted something here.

19:29.631 --> 19:47.570
I love to stress the sovereignty of God in the conversion of sinners and that human beings left to themselves are dead and blind and deaf and hard and rebellious and don't have the natural capacity

19:47.650 --> 19:55.239
to lift the little finger of their hand to make a move toward God, apart from grace.

19:56.300 --> 19:57.621
I love to exalt that.

19:58.743 --> 20:15.602
However, one can find himself exalting that direct, inner, illuminating, life-giving work of the Holy Spirit so much that you can easily neglect

20:15.778 --> 20:43.314
that the Holy Spirit has in a most stunning way submitted Himself to the Word of God in the performance of this life-giving divine act, so that He always follows around the Word of God like a shadow and never

20:44.354 --> 20:50.060
does his saving work in front of or without the word?

20:51.441 --> 21:01.191
That is, don't believe that any pagan tribe that has never heard the gospel has the Holy Spirit regenerating people in it.

21:01.832 --> 21:02.533
Don't believe it.

21:03.474 --> 21:11.762
And don't believe that the Holy Spirit just moves willy-nilly throughout the culture of America, saving this one and that one

21:11.874 --> 21:14.318
which maybe the Word will catch up to someday.

21:14.759 --> 21:16.041
That isn't the way it happens.

21:16.702 --> 21:26.619
The Holy Spirit moves like a shadow behind the Word of God, and there's a theological, biblical reason for that.

21:30.265 --> 21:37.778
Christ said that the Holy Spirit will be given to glorify me.

21:40.034 --> 21:46.765
I will send you a comforter, and his task will be to glorify me.

21:46.805 --> 22:00.366
Therefore, the Holy Spirit in utter allegiance to this mission given him by the Father and the Son will not quicken a heart to see nothing.

22:03.471 --> 22:07.858
He will only quicken hearts to see Christ.

22:08.674 --> 22:15.482
Therefore, if Christ is not placarded, the Holy Spirit will not open the eyes of the blind.

22:16.243 --> 22:19.206
He is utterly devoted to the glory of the Son.

22:20.027 --> 22:27.296
And therefore, when we preach the Son, the Holy Spirit comes and says, that is what I want people to see.

22:27.356 --> 22:29.218
I will open their eyes to it.

22:30.319 --> 22:36.306
And therefore, since there has to be life in the pew for there to be worship in the sanctuary,

22:37.058 --> 22:44.869
there has to be the Word in order for the Holy Spirit to move on the people to reveal the Word.

22:46.051 --> 23:04.436
There's a profound reason for why the Spirit being fully God and very God will not move on His own in regenerating people without the Word declaring the glory of the Son.

23:04.456 --> 23:05.778
So preach the Word.

23:06.370 --> 23:09.935
in the center of worship.

23:12.218 --> 23:22.734
Thank you for listening to this episode of Light and Truth, where we are committed to providing God-centered preaching to help you see Christ clearly and treasure Him truly.

23:23.314 --> 23:24.736
I'm your host, Dan Kruver.

23:25.578 --> 23:34.130
On our next episode, John Piper continues our eight-part series, Living and Dying for the Glory of Christ with a message titled,

23:34.306 --> 23:36.900
God's designed for the pulpit.

23:36.920 --> 23:37.725
I hope you'll join us.

23:38.851 --> 23:42.290
For more resources, visit desiringgod.org.

